snippet: Two Australians, Brady Watt and Oliver Goss, advanced to the United States Amateur semifinals in Brookline, Mass., along with Corey Conners of Canada and Matt Fitzpatrick of England.
abstract: Australian golfers Brady Watt and Oliver Goss advance to United States Amateur semifinals in Brookline, Mass; it is first Amateur in which no Americans reach final four; other golf news noted.
lead_paragraph: Two Australians, Brady Watt and Oliver Goss, advanced to the United States Amateur semifinals in Brookline, Mass., along with Corey Conners of Canada and Matt Fitzpatrick of England.
